.SH NAME
Types::Standard::Tuple \- exporter utility for the Tuple type constraint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&  use Types::Standard \-types;
\&  
\&  # Normal way to validate a pair of integers.
\&  #
\&  Tuple\->of( Int, Int )\->assert_valid( [ 7, 49 ] );
\&  
\&  use Types::Standard::Tuple IntPair => { of => [ Int, Int ] },
\&  
\&  # Exported shortcut
\&  #
\&  assert_IntPair [ 7, 49 ];
.Ve
.SH STATUS
.IX Header "STATUS"
This module is not covered by the
Type\-Tiny stability policy.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is mostly internal code, but can also act as an exporter utility.
.SS Exports
.IX Subsection "Exports"
Types::Standard::Tuple can be used experimentally as an exporter.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&  use Types::Standard \*(AqInt\*(Aq;
\&  use Types::Standard::Tuple IntPair => { of => [ Int, Int ] };
.Ve
.PP
This will export the following functions into your namespace:
.ie n .IP """IntPair""" 4
.el .IP \f(CWIntPair\fR 4
.IX Item "IntPair"
.PD 0
.ie n .IP "is_IntPair( $value )" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWis_IntPair( $value )\fR" 4
.IX Item "is_IntPair( $value )"
.ie n .IP "assert_IntPair( $value )" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWassert_IntPair( $value )\fR" 4
.IX Item "assert_IntPair( $value )"
.ie n .IP "to_IntPair( $value )" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWto_IntPair( $value )\fR" 4
.IX Item "to_IntPair( $value )"
.PD
.PP
Multiple types can be exported at once:
.PP
.Vb 5
\&  use Types::Standard \-types;
\&  use Types::Standard::HashRef (
\&    IntPair  => { of => [ Int, Int ] },
\&    StrInt   => { of => [ Str, Int ] },
\&  );
\&  
\&  assert_StrInt [ two => 2 ];   # should not die
.Ve
.PP
It\*(Aqs possible to further constrain the tuple using \f(CW\*(C`where\*(C'\fR:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&  use Types::Standard::Tuple MyThing => { of => [ ... ], where => sub { ... } };
.Ve
